comments.body:
@surlypants this is happening because you also have the "OpenSSH (mls-software)" chocolatey package installed which puts those shims in place. (https://chocolatey.org/packages/mls-software-openssh).

Please uninstall openssh (mls-software) with `choco install mls-software-openssh` and then ensure $env:chocolateyinstall\bin does NOT have any shims for any file like "ssh*.exe"

The OpenSSH package from the PowerShell open source project does not create shims (https://chocolatey.org/packages/openssh)

@iSazonov - this could be an ongoing issue for people who have installed more than one SSH client.  Maybe new-pssession should check and report on which ssh.exe it finds.  If PS remoting is only supported with Microsoft's ssh client - you could give a warning or an error.
